.TH TMUX-SAVE-SESSION 1 "2026-06-30" "tmux-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tmux-save-session \- save a tmux session layout as a restore script
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tmux-save-session
.RB [ -d
.IR dir | --dir
.IR dir ]
.RI [ session-name ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tmux-save-session
captures a tmux session's window names, pane layouts, pane working
directories, and active window into an executable restore script. When no
session name is supplied, the current tmux session is saved.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI -d ", --dir " dir
Directory where restore scripts are written.
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Show usage.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B TMUX_TOOLS_SESSION_DIR
Default session directory. If unset, the default is
.IR ${XDG_DATA_HOME:-$HOME/.local/share}/tmux/sessions .
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
The session was saved.
.TP
.B 1
tmux state could not be read or the restore script could not be written.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tmux-restore-session (1),
.BR tmux (1)
